    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter updating to Neovim v0.10.4, I now have strange behaviour on iTerm2 (on macOS) with special keys like Return and Escape: they only work if I add the Option modifier. This doesn't happen with other terminals (Alacritty, Terminal.app), and it doesn't happen in old-fashioned Vim with iTerm2. Only the combination of iTerm2 and Neovim (at least v0.10.4) yields the issue:\n\n| | Vim v9.1 | Neovim v0.10.4 |\n|-|-|-|\n| iTerm2 | normal | Need Option+Esc and Option+Return\n| Other terminal (Alacritty, Terminal.app) | normal | normal\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* run `nvim`\n* enter insert mode\n* press Return to add a new line: nothing happens\n* press Option+Return: a new line is added\n* press Escape: nothing happens\n* press Option+Escape: exit insert mode\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect Neovim to behave consistently in different terminals.\n\nI also expect Neovim's handling of Esc and Return to be consistent with Vim\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno,  9.1 (2024 Jan 02, compiled May 30 2024 12:20:54 by MacPorts)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.6.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
